===Etymology===
From {{etyl|non}} {{term|skil}}, distinction, adjustment, thence akin to Danish {{term|skel}}, border line (spelling before [[:w:de:Dänische Rechtschreibreform von 1948|the writing reform of 1948]]: {{term|Skjel}})

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/skɪl/}}, {{SAMPA|/skIl/}}
* {{audio|en-us-skill.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ɪl}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# [[capacity]] to do something well; [[technique]], [[ability]]. Skills are usually acquired or learned, as opposed to abilities, which are often thought of as innate.

